<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-07T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-07T09:00:00-05:00" n="771" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d771">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.01/19: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-07T11:00:00-03:00">March 7, 1936—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 7—10:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>91. My 85, March 2, 7 p.m. Have been informed in strictest confidence by
                            the Italian Ambassador that his Government has instructed the Italian
                            Minister at Asunción to say that recogition will be withheld until after
                            favorable action by mediatory powers.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>